89
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:10,270
Leave!

90
00:07:14,060 --> 00:07:16,570
Keep the fruits and eat them.

91
00:09:18,370 --> 00:09:20,240
Are you okay?

92
00:09:23,888 --> 00:09:26,077
You heard everything?

93
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:28,840
Not really.

94
00:09:30,490 --> 00:09:32,970
So the lady just now was...

95
00:09:32,970 --> 00:09:34,670
My mom.

96
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:39,330
I've never heard you mention your mom.

97
00:09:39,330 --> 00:09:41,340
Not on good terms?

98
00:09:42,890 --> 00:09:47,611
In over ten years, this is the first time we've seen each other.

99
00:09:54,920 --> 00:09:57,470
When I was a kid, my family was poor

100
00:09:58,110 --> 00:10:02,140
and every time I passed a claw machine, I wanted to play it.

101
00:10:02,140 --> 00:10:06,940
But my mom always told me those were all cheats.

102
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:09,322
No matter how many coins I put in,

103
00:10:09,322 --> 00:10:11,555
I couldn't catch anything.

104
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:15,730
Then one time I cried so hard,

105
00:10:15,730 --> 00:10:18,220
she comforted me and said

106
00:10:18,220 --> 00:10:22,670
she'd bring me there on my birthday for a good time.

107
00:10:23,330 --> 00:10:27,790
But she left before then

108
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:30,740
and never came back.

109
00:10:31,370 --> 00:10:36,140
For years after she left, I was asking for my mom every day.

110
00:10:36,850 --> 00:10:39,780
Then, my dad couldn't do anything about it,

111
00:10:39,780 --> 00:10:41,370
so he brought me there to catch dolls.

112
00:10:41,370 --> 00:10:43,350
He told me

113
00:10:43,890 --> 00:10:48,500
he'd take me to my mom if I could catch one.

114
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:50,600
Did you catch it?

115
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:54,630
No.

116
00:11:02,566 --> 00:11:04,860
But it didn’t matter anymore.

117
00:11:04,860 --> 00:11:06,630
Why?

118
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:12,320
Because my dad told me

119
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:14,717
she ran off with someone else.

120
00:11:18,190 --> 00:11:21,710
But today, she came to me and told me

121
00:11:21,710 --> 00:11:24,530
that my dad was at fault first.

122
00:11:25,350 --> 00:11:27,560
I'm confused.

123
00:11:29,540 --> 00:11:32,540
So she came over here today to tell you that?

124
00:11:32,540 --> 00:11:34,360
No.

125
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:38,140
She said she had some business difficulties

126
00:11:38,140 --> 00:11:40,360
and needed money.

127
00:11:43,370 --> 00:11:45,210
Funny, right?

128
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:48,620
First time seeing me after all these years,

129
00:11:48,620 --> 00:11:51,440
and she actually came to ask me for money.

130
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:55,870
Anyway, whether you admit it or not,

131
00:11:55,870 --> 00:11:58,570
you must still care about her.

132
00:12:05,440 --> 00:12:07,135
How about this?

133
00:12:10,640 --> 00:12:12,200
You go and play the claw machine again.

134
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:16,420
If you catch one this time, go and have a nice chat with her.

135
00:12:39,830 --> 00:12:44,380
When I couldn't catch a doll, I thought I was unlucky

136
00:12:44,380 --> 00:12:47,600
and couldn't get what I wanted.

137
00:12:50,590 --> 00:12:52,380
Now I've figured it out.

138
00:12:52,380 --> 00:12:55,440
If something doesn't belong to me,

139
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:57,630
