264
00:20:35,888 --> 00:20:38,222
The headquarters is in Beijing.

265
00:20:43,670 --> 00:20:46,540
Well, what do you think?

266
00:20:52,470 --> 00:20:54,820
I'm not sure now.

267
00:20:55,920 --> 00:20:58,740
But the opportunity is certainly a good one.

268
00:20:58,740 --> 00:21:02,844
Look, Mr. Jiang, Fu Ying, and Zhou Ye

269
00:21:02,844 --> 00:21:05,688
want me to think about it carefully.

270
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:11,340
But if I do decide to go,

271
00:21:12,020 --> 00:21:14,530
it's not three months away...

272
00:21:15,390 --> 00:21:17,260
It'll be three years.

273
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:29,580
Let's flip a coin and decide.

274
00:21:29,580 --> 00:21:31,440
Are you serious?

275
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:35,580
Aren't you going to Beijing for an interview?

276
00:21:35,580 --> 00:21:37,940
Heads means going by plane.

277
00:21:37,940 --> 00:21:39,910
And tails means going by train.

278
00:21:39,910 --> 00:21:41,740
I'll go with you.

279
00:21:41,740 --> 00:21:45,430
Whatever you choose, you'll have to go and see it, won't you?

280
00:21:45,430 --> 00:21:50,220
If something goes wrong, we'll run immediately. Okay?

281
00:21:52,770 --> 00:21:56,880
Let's try it. By plane or by train?

282
00:22:01,130 --> 00:22:04,710
Heads. It's expensive.

283
00:22:04,710 --> 00:22:06,780
Why don't we take a train?

284
00:22:07,990 --> 00:22:09,870
Take a plane.

285
00:22:09,870 --> 00:22:11,670
Let's take a train.

286
00:22:11,670 --> 00:22:12,910
The train would be nice.

287
00:22:12,910 --> 00:22:17,440
By train, I can still see the sights with you on the way.

288
00:22:24,870 --> 00:22:28,300
I didn't expect your company headquarters to be so big and luxurious.

289
00:22:28,300 --> 00:22:30,570
Right? This is the first time I've seen it too.

290
00:22:30,570 --> 00:22:33,460
This is a big city indeed.

291
00:22:35,740 --> 00:22:39,780
Don't you think I'm a bit sloppy in this outfit today?

292
00:22:39,780 --> 00:22:42,780
It's all right. Take it easy.

293
00:22:42,780 --> 00:22:44,670
Go upstairs.

294
00:22:45,355 --> 00:22:47,644
Aren't you coming with me?

295
00:22:49,020 --> 00:22:52,920
Take this. I'll wait for you here.

296
00:22:52,920 --> 00:22:55,050
I'll get going now. Go.

297
00:22:55,050 --> 00:22:56,922
I'll be right back.

298
00:22:58,230 --> 00:22:59,190
Bye.

299
00:22:59,190 --> 00:23:00,500
Piggy Jing, go for it.

300
00:23:00,500 --> 00:23:02,088
I can do it.

301
00:23:17,540 --> 00:23:19,850
We meet again, Jing.

302
00:23:19,850 --> 00:23:24,780
Dr. Gong, thank you for taking time out of your busy schedule to see me.

303
00:23:24,780 --> 00:23:27,430
Jing, what do you think about my offer?

304
00:23:27,430 --> 00:23:28,950
Thank you.

305
00:23:29,470 --> 00:23:33,880
Dr. Gong, well, I'm still considering it.

306
00:23:34,910 --> 00:23:35,870
It's okay.

307
00:23:35,870 --> 00:23:40,400
I've invited you here so you can see the Huan Dao headquarters

308
00:23:40,400 --> 00:23:42,933
and learn about our business structure.

309
00:23:42,933 --> 00:23:45,430
But you have to make a decision soon.

310
00:23:45,430 --> 00:23:49,020
As you can see, there are so many applicants out there

311
00:23:49,020 --> 00:23:51,670
trying to get in.

312
00:23:54,540 --> 00:23:57,000
Sorry. I'll take a call. Wait a minute.

313
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:58,430
Okay.

314
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:29,640
   

315
00:24:48,600 --> 00:24:50,100
Sorry to keep you waiting.

316
00:24:50,100 --> 00:24:51,990
I was just about to send you a message.

317
00:24:51,990 --> 00:24:54,660
Are you sure you went to a tech company, and not into some spider cave?

318
00:24:54,660 --> 00:24:56,122
It took you so long.

319
00:24:56,122 --> 00:24:57,870
Come on, there's no spider cave.

320
00:24:57,870 --> 00:24:59,400
How was it?

321
00:24:59,400 --> 00:25:01,145
I spent the afternoon listening to them describe

322
00:25:01,145 --> 00:25:04,260
their business and their strategy for the future.

323
00:25:04,260 --> 00:25:06,150
A big company is different indeed.

324
00:25:06,150 --> 00:25:09,530
Their business and layout really opened my eyes.

325
00:25:09,530 --> 00:25:12,720
Well, have you decided to stay?

326
00:25:13,340 --> 00:25:14,740
Not yet.

327
00:25:14,740 --> 00:25:16,300
But I do think

328
00:25:16,300 --> 00:25:21,530
Yangwu would get better development if it was at the headquarters.

329
00:25:23,370 --> 00:25:25,200
That's true.

330
00:25:29,060 --> 00:25:30,150
What's wrong?

331
00:25:30,150 --> 00:25:31,950
Nothing.

332
00:25:33,820 --> 00:25:38,790
I... I think Beijing is quite big.

333
00:25:55,780 --> 00:25:57,680
Let's go back.

334
00:26:00,670 --> 00:26:02,370
You're thinking of going back now?

335
00:26:02,370 --> 00:26:05,610
We're meeting Du Man and Song Cong for hot pot tonight.

336
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:11,230
Did you forget about it?

337
00:26:11,230 --> 00:26:13,850
Yes. I was too busy.

338
00:26:13,850 --> 00:26:15,488
- Let's go. 
 - Come on, quick.

339
00:26:15,488 --> 00:26:17,100
- Are they there yet? 
 - Yeah, already there.

340
00:26:17,100 --> 00:26:20,044
I've sent them a message asking them to wait for us.

341
00:26:21,990 --> 00:26:23,050
Add the vegetables.

342
00:26:23,050 --> 00:26:24,020
This too.

343
00:26:24,020 --> 00:26:25,250
Man.

344
00:26:25,250 --> 00:26:26,850
- Cong. 
 - Come on.

345
00:26:26,850 --> 00:26:28,430
It's almost cooked.

346
00:26:28,430 --> 00:26:30,260
- I'm starving. 
 - Come on.

347
00:26:30,260 --> 00:26:31,720
- Are you tired of interning now? 
 - A little.

348
00:26:31,720 --> 00:26:34,100
- Let me have a bite first. 
 - Come on, have some meat.

349
00:26:34,100 --> 00:26:35,110
It smells so good.

350
00:26:35,110 --> 00:26:37,077
I spend every day in the hospital.

351
00:26:37,077 --> 00:26:39,890
I even smell the disinfectant in this hot pot now.

352
00:26:39,890 --> 00:26:44,150
Dr. Du studies hard when she's studying, works hard when she's working,

353
00:26:44,150 --> 00:26:45,890
and is a top student everywhere.

354
00:26:45,890 --> 00:26:49,190
Dr. Song, with you around, I'm always the second best.

355
00:26:49,190 --> 00:26:52,200
Enough, you brainiacs.

356
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:54,780
Guess I’m doomed to be surrounded by overachievers my whole life.

357
00:26:54,780 --> 00:26:56,150
You flatter us.

358
00:26:56,150 --> 00:26:58,920
Maybe you'll be the first one among us to achieve your goal.

359
00:26:58,920 --> 00:27:02,890
Then I'll hire you high achievers to work for me.

360
00:27:02,890 --> 00:27:04,870
Who's working for who?

361
00:27:05,300 --> 00:27:07,440
I'll work for you.

362
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:10,000
- You want some vinegar? 
 - I want a Coke.

363
00:27:11,190 --> 00:27:13,500
When are you getting married?

364
00:27:18,810 --> 00:27:21,060
Who's marrying him?

365
00:27:21,060 --> 00:27:24,890
Chen Huan Er, can you save me some face in public?

366
00:27:29,044 --> 00:27:31,990
Come on. Have a bite.

367
00:27:33,120 --> 00:27:35,364
Come on, open your mouth.

368
00:27:39,960 --> 00:27:40,911
Dig in.

369
00:27:40,911 --> 00:27:43,100
Have they always been like this?

370
00:27:43,806 --> 00:27:45,720
They've already restrained themselves.

371
00:27:45,720 --> 00:27:48,677
You didn't see how mushy they were when they first got together.

372
00:27:48,677 --> 00:27:49,610
This is good.

373
00:27:49,610 --> 00:27:51,330
Not bad.

374
00:27:52,640 --> 00:27:54,114
Stop chatting, guys. Cheers.

375
00:27:54,114 --> 00:27:55,260
- Come on. 
 - Cheers.

376
00:27:55,260 --> 00:27:57,550
- Welcome. 
 - Thank you.

377
00:27:57,550 --> 00:27:59,820
- It's on me today. 
 - Then I'll order more.

378
00:27:59,820 --> 00:28:01,370
Go ahead.

379
00:28:14,580 --> 00:28:17,100
 Manman, I was wrong last time. 

380
00:28:17,100 --> 00:28:19,260
 I'm sorry. 

381
00:28:19,260 --> 00:28:21,060
 I won't ask you for money anymore. 

382
00:28:21,060 --> 00:28:24,870
 As long as you're well, I'm happy. 

383
00:28:26,580 --> 00:28:30,760
Man, it's been a long time since we last met.

384
00:28:30,760 --> 00:28:33,027
You're not going to have a nice chat with me?

385
00:28:34,990 --> 00:28:37,870
What do you want to ask? Go ahead.

386
00:28:37,870 --> 00:28:41,580
I'll ask but you can't be mad.

387
00:28:41,580 --> 00:28:46,340
Is it a coincidence that you and Cong

388
00:28:46,340 --> 00:28:49,670
live next door to each other?

389
00:28:51,910 --> 00:28:55,240
24K pure coincidence.

390
00:28:57,030 --> 00:29:02,260
But to be honest, you and Du Man have an amazing destiny.

391
00:29:02,260 --> 00:29:04,230
You went to high school together,

392
00:29:04,230 --> 00:29:06,610
then university together, and now that you graduated,

393
00:29:06,610 --> 00:29:09,060
you're interning at the same hospital.

394
00:29:09,060 --> 00:29:13,340
What's the word now? It's called a mutual destiny.

395
00:29:13,340 --> 00:29:14,740
Sounds like you two!

396
00:29:14,740 --> 00:29:16,920
All we can think about now is work.

397
00:29:16,920 --> 00:29:20,860
Enough. I know you very well.

398
00:29:22,240 --> 00:29:25,377
Is there something new going on at your new hospital?

399
00:29:25,377 --> 00:29:27,322
- Are you asking for a beating? 
 - I'll stop asking.

400
00:29:27,322 --> 00:29:29,060
Not talking about it.

401
00:29:33,230 --> 00:29:37,190
How was your visit to Huan Dao today?

402
00:29:38,200 --> 00:29:40,240
I haven't decided yet.

403
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:43,300
But I've been listening to them introduce their structure all afternoon.

404
00:29:43,300 --> 00:29:50,950
I think it might not be a bad thing to bring Yangwu here.

405
00:29:50,950 --> 00:29:53,370
If you really want to come, you can stay with me first.

406
00:29:53,370 --> 00:29:55,640
The rent here is not cheap.

407
00:29:55,640 --> 00:29:57,644
We'll see.

408
00:29:57,644 --> 00:30:00,340
By the way, did you talk to Huan Er?

409
00:30:00,340 --> 00:30:02,480
What does she think?

410
00:30:02,480 --> 00:30:05,100
Yangwu is his heart and soul.

411
00:30:05,100 --> 00:30:07,500
Of course I have to support him.

412
00:30:09,150 --> 00:30:11,100
But...

413
00:30:12,640 --> 00:30:15,320
It's just that he and I

414
00:30:15,320 --> 00:30:18,120
were never that far apart.

415
00:30:20,770 --> 00:30:25,020
So you're afraid you won't pass this first trial?

416
00:30:26,710 --> 00:30:29,000
I'm sure I can handle it.

417
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:31,480
I'm mostly worried about Huan Er.

418
00:30:31,480 --> 00:30:37,150
I can sense that she's afraid that our relationship will fade if we're far apart.

419
00:30:38,230 --> 00:30:41,430
Have you ever thought about why you created Yangwu?

420
00:30:42,200 --> 00:30:47,150
I did it in the first place to sell our high school review materials, didn't I?

421
00:30:47,150 --> 00:30:50,500
Who knew it could be possible?

422
00:30:50,500 --> 00:30:55,780
I now think that if there's a chance to give

423
00:30:55,780 --> 00:30:59,430
my mom and Huan Er a better life through Yangwu, why not?

424
00:30:59,430 --> 00:31:01,370
I need to make money.

425
00:31:01,370 --> 00:31:06,570
You're looking out for them, but they probably just want you to be happy too.

426
00:31:06,570 --> 00:31:08,100
Instead of making money,

427
00:31:08,100 --> 00:31:11,820
they want you to go after what you really want.

428
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:19,060
I don't know anything about relationships.

429
00:31:19,060 --> 00:31:21,540
But I think

430
00:31:22,670 --> 00:31:25,360
all relationships

431
00:31:25,360 --> 00:31:28,500
should be mutual,

432
00:31:28,500 --> 00:31:31,460
no matter if it's a family member

433
00:31:31,460 --> 00:31:33,270
or a lover.

434
00:31:34,150 --> 00:31:36,300
Mutual tolerance,

435
00:31:36,300 --> 00:31:38,500
and mutual trust.

436
00:31:39,090 --> 00:31:44,440
I think this is the meaning of an intimate relationship.

437
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:51,230
I agree with you.

438
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:55,740
Thank you, Du Man.

439
00:31:55,740 --> 00:31:57,540
What for?

440
00:32:02,870 --> 00:32:04,720
Sleep early.

441
00:32:04,720 --> 00:32:06,740
- Okay, let's sleep early. 
 - Let's sleep.

442
00:32:06,740 --> 00:32:09,215
I'll turn off the light.

443
00:32:10,740 --> 00:32:13,100
- Good night. 
 - Good night.

444
00:32:18,820 --> 00:32:20,860
   

445
00:32:22,860 --> 00:32:25,340
   

446
00:32:43,660 --> 00:32:45,940
    
    

